description:
Set 1

Alabama Getaway-> Greatest Story Ever Told, Dire Wolf-> CC Rider, Bird Song, It's All Over Now, Loser, Minglewood Blues, China Cat Sunflower-> I Know You Rider

Set 2

Women Are Smarter, To Lay Me Down, Lost Sailor-> Saint Of Circumstance-> Drums-> The Other One-> Stella Blue-> Goin' Down The Road Feelin' Bad-> Satisfaction, E: Brokedown Palace

reviews.review_text:
Rochester 4/9/82 Smokin' Show! After a standard bama>greatest story opener, this show rips. Definitely one of the best Birdsongs I've ever heard,and from there the first set is a blaze of fire all the way through to Chinarider. In the second set, To Lay Me Down is to cry for. The boys are decidedly "on" this night. The bring the thunder in the Other One and Stella Blue is delicate and soaring. Goin Down the Road and Satisfaction are spot on. Brokedown Palace had to send the audience home with a smile. 
Very clean audience recording. Congrats and thanks to Jim Vita et al.

Classic GD This was my 5th show and the ONE that truly cemented it all for me! Killer first set, a lot of standards, but so well played. Amazing how good JG/BW vioces were in 81/82! Great Loser, ALL over Now, Birdsong, GDTRFB! The Boys definitely played well in Roch!

Choice show and AUD This is really nice, particularly Birdsong, To Lay Me Down, and Stella Blue.

It is an excellent tape too-- Vita did good work.
